{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/make/robot/prototype-2.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"plans-for-version-2\" style=\"position:relative;\">Plans for version 2<a href=\"#plans-for-version-2\" aria-label=\"plans for version 2 permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>battery level indicator (LCD + DAC converter)</li>\n<li>130 Ohm resistors for LEDs instead of 470 Ohm</li>\n<li>optional remote charger</li>\n<li>get power straight from PSU when in charge mode (something like <a href=\"https://www.ti.com/lit/ds/symlink/tps2113.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TPS2113</a>)</li>\n<li>add to power board logic level 3.3V</li>\n<li>brushless DC motors</li>\n<li>look into adjustable output regulator based on <a href=\"https://datasheetspdf.com/pdf-file/1045179/STMicroelectronics/78M12/1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">L78M</a> and <a href=\"https://datasheetspdf.com/pdf-file/237025/SGS/LS141/1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">LS141</a></li>\n<li>choose an MCU. Forget about ATMega and RP2040, they don't have integrated battery management, that's why look into <a href=\"https://www.seeedstudio.com/Seeed-XIAO-BLE-nRF52840-p-5201.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">nRF52840</a></li>\n<li>LCD screen. What is refresh rate on LCD screen with SPI protocol?</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"control-voltage-with-microcontroller\" style=\"position:relative;\">Control voltage with microcontroller<a href=\"#control-voltage-with-microcontroller\" aria-label=\"control voltage with microcontroller permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Good ref: <a href=\"https://www.analog.com/en/technical-articles/digital-adjustment-of-dcdc-converter-output-voltage-in-portable-applications.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.analog.com/en/technical-articles/digital-adjustment-of-dcdc-converter-output-voltage-in-portable-applications.html</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"digitally-adjustable-boost-converter\" style=\"position:relative;\">Digitally Adjustable Boost Converter<a href=\"#digitally-adjustable-boost-converter\" aria-label=\"digitally adjustable boost converter permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<p>Like <a href=\"https://www.ti.com/lit/ds/symlink/tps61045.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TPS61045</a> or <a href=\"https://www.pacificdisplay.com/ics_app%20notes/dc-dc%20converters/MAX686.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MAX686</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"digipots-and-opamp\" style=\"position:relative;\">Digipots and opamp<a href=\"#digipots-and-opamp\" aria-label=\"digipots and opamp permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<p>MCU controllable resistor - digital potentiometer (aka digipot)</p>\n<p>Tweaking <a href=\"https://www.electronicdesign.com/technologies/analog/article/21801191/extend-lowvoltage-digipot-resolution-to-control-an-adjustable-regulator\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.electronicdesign.com/technologies/analog/article/21801191/extend-lowvoltage-digipot-resolution-to-control-an-adjustable-regulator</a></p>\n<p>FAQ <a href=\"https://www.analog.com/en/app-notes/an-1291.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.analog.com/en/app-notes/an-1291.html</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"dac\" style=\"position:relative;\">DAC<a href=\"#dac\" aria-label=\"dac permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In general if you are not using a digital pot to handle an analog signal originating off-board, you don't need the digital pot, a DAC is the simplest approach. DACs are much more numerous and easy to source too.</p>\n<p>MarkT</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"pwm\" style=\"position:relative;\">PWM<a href=\"#pwm\" aria-label=\"pwm permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The high-frequency switching of the PWM output stage consumes much more power than a low-power DAC or digital trim pot, both of which are DC by nature.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Cascade of resistor dividers and mosfets\nMotorized potentiometer</p>\n<h2 id=\"lcd\" style=\"position:relative;\">LCD<a href=\"#lcd\" aria-label=\"lcd permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"Plans for version 2 battery level indicator (LCD + DAC converter) 130 Ohm resistors for LEDs instead of 470 Ohm optional remote charger get…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#plans-for-version-2\">Plans for version 2</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#control-voltage-with-microcontroller\">Control voltage with microcontroller</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#digitally-adjustable-boost-converter\">Digitally Adjustable Boost Converter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#digipots-and-opamp\">Digipots and opamp</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#dac\">DAC</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pwm\">PWM</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#lcd\">LCD</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"December 26, 2022","published":"December 26, 2022","lastModified":"December 26, 2022","title":"Prototype 2","subtitle":null,"section":"robot","draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/make/robot/prototype-2.md","url":"/make/robot/prototype-2","next":{"excerpt":"For the first version let's keep this part simple and we will limit sensors to motor encoders proximity sensor (ultrasonic) accelerometer","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/make/robot/sensor-board.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Sensor board","date":"2023-02-13T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"652c2f8f-7d5e-5b75-aef1-da78c754a8af"},"previous":{"excerpt":"YMFC-AL ? YMFC Open S